## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## NexuzyAI-Android  —  local.properties template
## Copy this file to local.properties (git-ignored)
## Fill in your own API keys below
## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## Android SDK path (set automatically by Android Studio)
sdk.dir=/Users/YourName/Library/Android/sdk

## ── Google Maps + Geocoding API ──────────────────────────
## 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
## 2. Create project → Enable:
##      • Maps SDK for Android   (MapView, markers)
##      • Geocoding API          (GPS → city name)
## 3. Create API Key → restrict to package: ai.nexuzy.assistant + your SHA-1
MAPS_API_KEY=YOUR_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_HERE

## ── NewsAPI ───────────────────────────────────────────────
## Get free key at https://newsapi.org
NEWS_API_KEY=YOUR_NEWS_API_KEY_HERE

## ── Sarvaam AI API (cloud AI fallback when internet on) ───
## Get API key at https://sarvam.ai
## When set: AI uses Sarvaam API for responses when internet available
## Improves accuracy significantly over offline-only mode
## Leave blank to use DuckDuckGo search context only
SARVAAM_API_KEY=YOUR_SARVAAM_API_KEY_HERE

## ── AdMob (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────
## Get IDs at https://admob.google.com
## Leave as test IDs during development:
ADMOB_APP_ID=ca-app-pub-3940256099942544~3347511713
ADMOB_BANNER_ID=ca-app-pub-3940256099942544/6300978111
